            <dd class="answer">
                <p>World <img class="du1" src="img/du1.gif"> I (WWI or WW1), also known as the First World <img class="du1" src="img/du1.gif">, the Great War, or the War to End All Wars, was a <img class="globe" src="img/worldwar1/globe.gif"> war originating in Europe that lasted from 28 July 1914 to 11 November 1918. More than 70 million <img class="du1" src="img/du1.gif"> personnel, including 60 million Europeans, were mobilised in one of the largest <img class="du1" src="img/du1.gif"> in <img class="history" src="img/worldwar1/history.gif">. Over nine million <img class="army2" src="img/army2.gif"> and seven million civilians <img class="dead" src="img/dead.gif"> as a result of the war (including the victims of a number of genocides), a casualty rate exacerbated by the belligerents' technological and <img class="train" src="img/train.gif"> sophistication, and the tactical stalemate caused by gruelling trench warfare. It was one of the <img class="dead" src="img/dead.gif"> conflicts in <img class="history" src="img/worldwar1/history.gif">, and paved the <img src="img/way.gif"> for major political changes, including revolutions in many of the nations involved.</p>
            </dd>
