        <dl>
            <dt>Russian Civil War</dt>
            <dd class="answer">
                <p>The Russian Civil <img class="du1" src="img/du1.gif"> (Russian: Гражда́нская война́ в Росси́и, tr. Grazhdanskaya voyna v Rossiy; November 1917 – October 1922) was a multi-<img src="img/party2.gif"> <img class="du1" src="img/du1.gif"> in the former Russian empire immediately after the Russian Revolutions of 1917, as many factions vied to determine Russia's political future. The two largest <img class="army2" src="img/army2.gif"> groups were the Red <img class="army2" src="img/army2.gif">, fighting for the Bolshevik form of socialism, and the loosely allied forces known as the White <img class="army3" src="img/army3.gif">, which included diverse interests favoring monarchism, capitalism and alternative forms of socialism, each with democratic and antidemocratic variants. In addition, rival militant socialists and nonideological Green <img class="army3" src="img/army3.gif"> fought against both the Bolsheviks and the Whites. Eight foreign nations intervened against the Red <img class="army2" src="img/army2.gif">, notably the Allied Forces and the pro-German armies. The Red <img class="army2" src="img/army2.gif"> defeated the White <img class="army3" src="img/army3.gif"> Forces of South Russia in Ukraine and the <img class="army2" src="img/army2.gif"> led by Admiral Aleksandr Kolchak in Siberia in 1919. The remains of the White forces commanded by Pyotr Nikolayevich Wrangel were beaten in Crimea and evacuated in late 1920. Lesser <img class="du1" src="img/du1.gif"> of the <img class="du1" src="img/du1.gif"> continued on the periphery for two more years, and minor skirmishes with the remnants of the White forces in the Far East continued well into 1923. <img class="army2" src="img/army2.gif"> national resistance in Central Asia was not completely crushed until 1934. There were an estimated 7,000,000–12,000,000 <img class="dead" src="img/dead.gif"> during the <img class="du1" src="img/du1.gif">, mostly civilians. The Russian Civil <img class="du1" src="img/du1.gif"> has been described by some as the greatest national catastrophe that Europe had yet seen.</p>
            </dd>
