            <dt>Chinese Civil War</dt>
            <dd class="answer">
                <p>The <img class="china" src="img/china.gif"> Civil War was fought between forces <img class="loyal" src="img/loyal.gif"> to the Kuomintang (KMT)-led government of the Republic of <img class="china" src="img/china.gif">, and forces <img class="loyal" src="img/loyal.gif"> to the Communist <img src="img/party2.gif"> of <img class="china" src="img/china.gif"> (CPC). The civil war began in August 1927, with Generalissimo Chiang Kai-shek's Northern Expedition, and essentially ended when major hostilities ceased in 1950. It can generally be <img src="img/moses2.gif"> into two stages; the first being from 1927 to 1937, and the second being from 1946 to 1950 with the Second Sino-Japanese War <img src="img/moses.gif"> them. The war was a major turning point in modern <img class="china" src="img/china.gif"> <img class="history" src="img/worldwar1/history.gif">, with the CPC gaining control of almost the entirety of <img class="land" src="img/land.gif">  <img class="china" src="img/china.gif">, establishing the People's Republic of <img class="china" src="img/china.gif"> (PRC) to replace the KMT's Republic of <img class="china" src="img/china.gif"> (ROC). It also caused a lasting political and <img class="army2" src="img/army2.gif"> standoff between the two sides of the Taiwan Strait, with the ROC in Taiwan and the PRC in <img class="land" src="img/land.gif"> <img class="china" src="img/china.gif"> both officially claiming to be the legitimate government of all of <img class="china" src="img/china.gif">.</p>
            </dd>
        </dl>
