            <dt>Korean War</dt>
            <dd class="answer">
                <p><img class="korea" src="img/korea.gif"> was ruled by Japan from 1910 until the closing days of <img class="globe" src="img/worldwar1/globe.gif"> <img class="du1" src="img/du1.gif"> II. In August 1945, the Soviet Union declared <img class="du1" src="img/du1.gif"> on Japan, as a result of an agreement with the United States, and liberated <img src="img/north.gif"> of the 38th parallel. <img class="america" src="img/america.gif"> forces subsequently moved into the south. By 1948, as a product of the <img class="cold" src="img/cold.gif"> <img class="du1" src="img/du1.gif"> between the Soviet Union and the United States, <img class="korea" src="img/korea.gif">  was <img src="img/moses.gif">  into two regions, with separate governments. Both governments claimed to be the legitimate government of all of <img class="korea" src="img/korea.gif">, and neither side accepted the border as permanent. The conflict escalated into open warfare when <img src="img/north.gif"> forces—supported by the Soviet Union and <img class="china" src="img/china.gif">—moved into the south on 25 June 1950. On that day, the <img class="america" src="img/america.gif"> <img class="security" src="img/security.gif"> Council recognized this <img src="img/north.gif"> act as <img class="tank" src="img/tank.gif"> and called for an immediate ceasefire. On 27 June, the <img class="security" src="img/security.gif"> Council adopted S/RES/83: Complaint of aggression upon the Republic of <img class="korea" src="img/korea.gif"> and decided the formation and dispatch of the UN Forces in <img class="korea" src="img/korea.gif">. Twenty-one countries of the United Nations eventually contributed to the UN force, with the United States providing 88% of the UN's <img class="army2" src="img/army2.gif"> personnel.</p>
