        <dl>
            <dt>Algerian War</dt>
            <dd class="answer">
                <p>The Algerian <img class="du1" src="img/du1.gif">, also known as the Algerian <img class="du1" src="img/du1.gif"> of Independence or the Algerian Revolution (Arabic: الثورة الجزائرية‎‎ Al-thawra Al-Jazaa'iriyya;, Berber: Tagrawla Tadzayrit;, French: Guerre d'Algérie or Révolution algérienne) was a <img class="du1" src="img/du1.gif"> between France and the Algerian National Liberation Front (French: Front de Libération Nationale - FLN) from 1954 to 1962, which led to Algeria gaining its independence from France. An important decolonization <img class="du1" src="img/du1.gif">, it was a complex conflict characterized by guerrilla warfare, maquis <img class="du1" src="img/du1.gif">, and the use of torture by both sides. The conflict also became a civil <img class="du1" src="img/du1.gif"> between <img class="loyal" src="img/loyal.gif"> Algerians supporting a French Algeria and their Algerian nationalist counterparts.</p>
            </dd>
        </dl>
