        <dl>
            <dt>Vietnam War</dt>
            <dd class="answer">
                <p>The Vietnam <img class="du1" src="img/du1.gif"> (Vietnamese: Chiến tranh Việt Nam), also known as the Second Indochina <img class="du1" src="img/du1.gif">, and known in Vietnam as Resistance <img class="du1" src="img/du1.gif"> Against <img class="america" src="img/america.gif"> (Vietnamese: Kháng chiến chống Mỹ) or simply the <span class="america"><img src="img/america.gif"></span> <img class="du1" src="img/du1.gif">, was a <img class="du1" src="img/du1.gif"> that occurred in Vietnam, Laos, and Cambodia from 1 November 1955 to the fall of Saigon on 30 April 1975. It was the second of the Indochina <img class="du1" src="img/du1.gif"> and was officially fought between North Vietnam and the government of South Vietnam. The North Vietnamese <img class="army2" src="img/army2.gif"> was supported by the Soviet Union, <img class="china" src="img/china.gif"> and other communist allies and the South Vietnamese <img class="army2" src="img/army2.gif"> was supported by the <img class="america" src="img/america.gif">, <img class="korea" src="img/korea.gif">, Australia, Thailand and other anti-communist allies.The <img class="du1" src="img/du1.gif"> is therefore considered a <img class="cold" src="img/cold.gif"> War-era proxy <img class="du1" src="img/du1.gif">.</p>
            </dd>
